[Term]
id: CDT:0000120
name: billing code D0120: periodic oral evaluation - established patient
is_a: CDT:1000015 ! billing code for clinical oral evaluations
disjoint_from: CDT:0000140 ! billing code D0140: limited oral evaluation - problem focused
relationship: IAO:0000136 OHD:0000198 ! is about periodic oral evaluation
property_value: cdt:label "periodic oral evaluation - established patient" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D0120" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "An evaluation performed on a patient of record to determine any changes in the patients dental and medical health status since a previous comprehensive or periodic evaluation. This includes an oral cancer evaluation and periodontal screening where indicated, and may require interpretation of information acquired through additional diagnostic procedures. Report additional diagnostic procedures separately. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:0000140
name: billing code D0140: limited oral evaluation - problem focused
is_a: CDT:1000015 ! billing code for clinical oral evaluations
relationship: IAO:0000136 OHD:0000201 ! is about limited oral evaluation
property_value: cdt:label "limited oral evaluation - problem focused" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D0140" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "An evaluation limited to a specific oral health problem or complaint. This may require interpretation of information acquired through additional diagnostic procedures. Report additional diagnostic procedures separately. Definitive procedures may be required on the same date as the evaluation.\nTypically, patients receiving this type of evaluation present with a specific problem and/or dental emergencies, trauma, acute infections, etc. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:0000150
name: billing code D0150: comprehensive oral evaluation - new or established patient
is_a: CDT:1000015 ! billing code for clinical oral evaluations
relationship: IAO:0000136 OHD:0000202 ! is about comprehensive oral evaluation
property_value: cdt:label "comprehensive oral evaluation - new or established patient" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D0150" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Used by a general dentist and/or a specialist when evaluating a patient comprehensively.  This applies to new patients; established patients\nwho have had a significant change  in health conditions or other unusual circumstances, by report, or established patients who have been absent from active treatment for three or more years. It is a thorough evaluation\nand recording of the extraoral and intraoral hard and soft tissues. It may require interpretation of information acquired through additional diagnostic procedures.  Additional diagnostic procedures  should be reported separately.\nThis includes an evaluation for oral cancer where indicated, the evaluation and recording of the patients dental and medical history and a general health assessment.  It may include the evaluation and recording of dental caries, missing or unerupted teeth, restorations, existing prostheses, occlusal relationships, periodontal conditions (including periodontal screening and/or charting), hard and soft tissue anomalies, etc. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:0000160
name: billing code D0160: detailed and extensive  oral evaluation - problem focused, by report
is_a: CDT:1000015 ! billing code for clinical oral evaluations
property_value: cdt:label "detailed and extensive  oral evaluation - problem focused, by report" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D0160" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "A detailed and extensive problem focused evaluation entails extensive diagnostic and cognitive modalities based on the findings of a comprehensive oral evaluation. Integration of more extensive diagnostic modalities to develop a treatment  plan for a specific problem is required. The condition requiring this type of evaluation should be described and documented.\nExamples of conditions requiring this type of evaluation may include dentofacial anomalies, complicated perio-prosthetic  conditions, complex temporomandibular dysfunction, facial pain of unknown origin, conditions requiring multi-disciplinary consultation, etc. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "A narrative explaining the treatment provided must be included with a claim submission that uses this code.  \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:0000180
name: billing code D0180: comprehensive periodontal evaluation - new or established patient
is_a: CDT:1000015 ! billing code for clinical oral evaluations
relationship: IAO:0000136 OHD:0000203 ! is about comprehensive periodontal evaluation
property_value: cdt:label "comprehensive periodontal evaluation - new or established patient" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D0180" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "This procedure  is indicated for patients showing signs or symptoms of periodontal disease and for patients with risk factors such as smoking\nor diabetes.  It includes evaluation of periodontal conditions, probing and charting, evaluation and recording of the patients dental and medical history and general health assessment.  It may include the evaluation\nand recording of dental caries, missing or unerupted teeth, restorations, occlusal relationships and oral cancer evaluation. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:0001351
name: billing code D1351: sealant - per tooth
is_a: CDT:1000025 ! billing code for other preventive services
property_value: cdt:label "sealant - per tooth" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D1351" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Mechanically and/or chemically prepared enamel surface sealed to prevent decay. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:0001352
name: billing code D1352: preventive resin restoration in a moderate to high caries risk patient - permanent tooth
is_a: CDT:1000025 ! billing code for other preventive services
property_value: cdt:label "preventive resin restoration in a moderate to high caries risk patient - permanent tooth" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D1352" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Conservative restoration of an active cavitated  lesion in a pit or fissure that does not extend into dentin; includes placement of a sealant in any radiating non-carious fissures or pits. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

