[Term]
id: CDT:0002794
name: billing code D2794: crown - titanium
is_a: CDT:1000023 ! billing code for crowns - single restorations only
relationship: IAO:0000136 OHD:0000140 ! is about titanium crown restoration procedure
property_value: cdt:label "crown - titanium" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D2794" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:0002799
name: billing code D2799: provisional crown
is_a: CDT:1000023 ! billing code for crowns - single restorations only
property_value: cdt:label "provisional crown" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D2799" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Crown utilized as an interim restoration  of at least six months duration during restorative treatment to allow adequate time for healing or completion of other procedures.  This includes, but is not limited to changing vertical dimension, completing periodontal therapy or cracked-tooth  syndrome. This is not to be used as a temporary crown for a routine prosthetic restoration. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:0002931
name: billing code D2931: prefabricated stainless steel crown - permanent tooth
is_a: CDT:1000026 ! billing code for other restorative services
relationship: IAO:0000136 OHD:0000163 ! is about stainless steel crown restoration procedure
property_value: cdt:label "prefabricated stainless steel crown - permanent tooth" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D2931" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:0002932
name: billing code D2932: prefabricated resin crown
is_a: CDT:1000026 ! billing code for other restorative services
relationship: IAO:0000136 OHD:0000199 ! is about prefabricated resin crown restoration procedure
property_value: cdt:label "prefabricated resin crown" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D2932" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:0002933
name: billing code D2933: prefabricated stainless steel crown with resin window
is_a: CDT:1000026 ! billing code for other restorative services
relationship: IAO:0000136 OHD:0000164 ! is about stainless steel with resin window crown restoration procedure
property_value: cdt:label "prefabricated stainless steel crown with resin window" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D2933" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Open-face stainless steel crown with aesthetic resin facing or veneer. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:0002940
name: billing code D2940: protective restoration
is_a: CDT:1000026 ! billing code for other restorative services
property_value: cdt:label "protective restoration" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D2940" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Direct placement of a temporary restorative material to protect tooth and/ or tissue form. This procedure may be used to relieve pain, promote healing, or prevent further deterioration. Not to be used for endodontic access closure, or as a base or liner under a restoration. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:0002950
name: billing code D2950: core buildup, including any pins
is_a: CDT:1000026 ! billing code for other restorative services
property_value: cdt:label "core buildup, including any pins" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D2950" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Refers to building up of anatomical crown when restorative crown will be placed, whether  or not pins are used. A material is placed in the tooth preparation for\na crown when there is insufficient tooth strength and retention for the crown procedure. This should not be reported when the procedure only involves a filler to eliminate any undercut, box form, or concave  irregularity in the preparation. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:0002952
name: billing code D2952: post and core in addition to crown, indirectly fabricated
is_a: CDT:1000026 ! billing code for other restorative services
property_value: cdt:label "post and core in addition to crown, indirectly fabricated" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D2952" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Post and core are custom fabricated as a single unit. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:0002954
name: billing code D2954: prefabricated post and core in addition to crown
is_a: CDT:1000026 ! billing code for other restorative services
property_value: cdt:label "prefabricated post and core in addition to crown" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D2954" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Core is built around a prefabricated post. This procedure includes the core material. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:0002960
name: billing code D2960: labial veneer (resin laminate) - chairside
is_a: CDT:1000026 ! billing code for other restorative services
relationship: IAO:0000136 OHD:0000045 ! is about resin laminate veneer restoration procedure
property_value: cdt:label "labial veneer (resin laminate) - chairside" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D2960" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Refers to labial/facial direct resin bonded veneers. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:0002961
name: billing code D2961: labial veneer (resin laminate) - laboratory
is_a: CDT:1000026 ! billing code for other restorative services
relationship: IAO:0000136 OHD:0000045 ! is about resin laminate veneer restoration procedure
property_value: cdt:label "labial veneer (resin laminate) - laboratory" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D2961" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Refers to labial/facial indirect resin bonded veneers. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:0002962
name: billing code D2962: labial veneer (porcelain laminate) - laboratory
is_a: CDT:1000026 ! billing code for other restorative services
relationship: IAO:0000136 OHD:0000046 ! is about porcelain laminate veneer restoration procedure
property_value: cdt:label "labial veneer (porcelain laminate) - laboratory" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D2962" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Refers also to facial veneers that extend interproximally and/or cover the incisal edge. Porcelain/ceramic  veneers  presently  include all ceramic and porcelain veneers. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:0002970
name: billing code D2970: temporary crown (fractured tooth)
is_a: CDT:1000026 ! billing code for other restorative services
property_value: cdt:label "temporary crown (fractured tooth)" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D2970" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Usually a preformed artificial crown, which is fitted over a damaged tooth as an immediate protective  device. This is not to be used as temporization during crown fabrication. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:0003220
name: billing code D3220: therapeutic pulpotomy (excluding final restoration) - removal of pulp coronal to the dentinocemental junction and application of medicament
is_a: CDT:1000020 ! billing code for pulpotomy
property_value: cdt:label "therapeutic pulpotomy (excluding final restoration) - removal of pulp coronal to the dentinocemental junction and application of medicament" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D3220" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Pulpotomy is the surgical removal of a portion of the pulp with the aim of maintaining the vitality of the remaining portion by means of an adequate dressing.\n To be performed on primary or permanent teeth.\n This is not to be construed as the first stage of root canal therapy.\n Not to be used for apexogenesis. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:0003221
name: billing code D3221: pulpal debridement, primary and permanent teeth
is_a: CDT:1000020 ! billing code for pulpotomy
property_value: cdt:label "pulpal debridement, primary and permanent teeth" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D3221" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Pulpal debridement  for the relief of acute pain prior to conventional root canal therapy. This procedure  is not to be used when endodontic treatment is completed  on the same day. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:0003222
name: billing code D3222: partial pulpotomy for apexogenesis - permanent tooth with incomplete root development
is_a: CDT:1000020 ! billing code for pulpotomy
property_value: cdt:label "partial pulpotomy for apexogenesis - permanent tooth with incomplete root development" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D3222" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Removal of a portion of the pulp and application of a medicament with the aim of maintaining the vitality of the remaining portion to encourage continued physiological development and formation of the root. This procedure is not to be construed as the first stage of root canal therapy. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:0003310
name: billing code D3310: endodontic therapy,  anterior tooth (excluding final restoration)
is_a: CDT:1000011 ! billing code for endodontic therapy (including treatment plan, clinical procedures and follow-up care)
property_value: cdt:label "endodontic therapy,  anterior tooth (excluding final restoration)" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D3310" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:0003320
name: billing code D3320: endodontic therapy,  bicuspid tooth (excluding final restoration)
is_a: CDT:1000011 ! billing code for endodontic therapy (including treatment plan, clinical procedures and follow-up care)
property_value: cdt:label "endodontic therapy,  bicuspid tooth (excluding final restoration)" xsd:string
property_value: dc:identifier "D3320" xsd:string

[Term]
