property_value: editor_note "This is typically reported  on a per visit basis for emergency treatment of dental pain. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:1000001
name: current dental terminology code
comment: A current dental terminology code is a centrally registered identifier that is maintained by the American Dental Association and used for recording dental services provided. It is typically used on the patient record, and when reporting procedures on a paper or electronic submission. 
is_a: IAO:0000578 ! centrally registered identifier

[Term]
id: CDT:1000002
name: billing code for amalgam restorations (including polishing)
is_a: CDT:1000022 ! billing code for restorative
relationship: IAO:0000136 OHD:0000041 ! is about amalgam filling restoration procedure
property_value: cdt:label "amalgam restorations (including polishing)" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Tooth preparation, all adhesives (including amalgam bonding agents), liners and bases\nare included as part of the restoration. If pins are used, they should be reported\nseparately (see D2951). \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:1000003
