id: CDT:1000007
name: billing code for adjunctive general services
is_a: CDT:1000001 ! current dental terminology code
property_value: cdt:label "adjunctive general services" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:1000008
name: billing code for inlay/onlay restorations
is_a: CDT:1000022 ! billing code for restorative
property_value: cdt:label "inlay/onlay restorations" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:1000009
name: billing code for other endodontic procedures
is_a: CDT:1000030 ! billing code for endodontics
property_value: cdt:label "other endodontic procedures" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:1000010
name: billing code for inlay/onlay restorations - resin-based composite
is_a: CDT:1000008 ! billing code for inlay/onlay restorations
property_value: cdt:label "inlay/onlay restorations - resin-based composite" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Resin-based composite inlays/onlays must utilize indirect technique. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:1000011
name: billing code for endodontic therapy (including treatment plan, clinical procedures and follow-up care)
is_a: CDT:1000030 ! billing code for endodontics
property_value: cdt:label "endodontic therapy (including treatment plan, clinical procedures and follow-up care)" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Includes primary teeth without succedaneous teeth and permanent teeth. Complete\nroot canal therapy; pulpectomy is part of root canal therapy.\nIncludes all appointments necessary to complete treatment; also includes intra-operative\nradiographs. Does not include diagnostic evaluation and necessary radiographs/diagnostic\nimages. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:1000012
name: billing code for other fixed partial denture services
is_a: CDT:1000005 ! billing code for prosthodontics, fixed
property_value: cdt:label "other fixed partial denture services" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:1000013
name: billing code for resin-based composite restorations - direct
is_a: CDT:1000022 ! billing code for restorative
property_value: cdt:label "resin-based composite restorations - direct" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Resin-based composite refers to a broad category of materials including but not\nlimited to composites. May include bonded composite, light-cured composite, etc.\nTooth preparation, acid etching, adhesives (including resin bonding agents), liners\nand bases and curing are included as part of the restoration. Glass ionomers, when\nused as restorations, should be reported with these codes. If pins are used, they\nshould be reported separately (see D2951). \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:1000014
name: billing code for inlay/onlay restorations - porcelain/ceramic
is_a: CDT:1000008 ! billing code for inlay/onlay restorations
property_value: cdt:label "inlay/onlay restorations - porcelain/ceramic" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Porcelain/ceramic inlays/onlays include all indirect ceramic and porcelain type\ninlays/onlays. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:1000015
name: billing code for clinical oral evaluations
is_a: CDT:1000027 ! billing code for diagnostic
property_value: cdt:label "clinical oral evaluations" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "The codes in this section recognize the cognitive skills necessary for patient evaluation.\nThe collection and recording of some data and components of the dental examination\nmay be delegated; however, the evaluation, which includes diagnosis and treatment\nplanning, is the responsibility of the dentist. As with all ADA procedure codes, there\nis no distinction made between the evaluations provided by general practitioners and\nspecialists. Report additional diagnostic and/or definitive procedures separately. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:1000016
name: billing code for surgical extractions (includes local anesthesia, suturing, if needed, and routine postoperative care)
is_a: CDT:1000017 ! billing code for oral and maxillofacial surgery
property_value: cdt:label "surgical extractions (includes local anesthesia, suturing, if needed, and routine postoperative care)" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:1000017
name: billing code for oral and maxillofacial surgery
is_a: CDT:1000001 ! current dental terminology code
property_value: cdt:label "oral and maxillofacial surgery" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Local anesthesia is usually considered to be part of Oral and Maxillofacial Surgical\nprocedures.\nFor dental benefit reporting purposes a quadrant is defined as four or more contiguous\nteeth and/or teeth spaces distal to the midline. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

