[Term]
id: CDT:1000028
name: billing code for apicoectomy/periradicular services
is_a: CDT:1000030 ! billing code for endodontics
property_value: cdt:label "apicoectomy/periradicular services" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Periradicular surgery is a term used to describe surgery to the root surface (e.g.,\napicoectomy), repair of a root perforation or resorptive defect, exploratory curettage\nto look for root fractures, removal of extruded filling materials or instruments,\nremoval of broken root fragments, sealing of accessory canals, etc. This does not\ninclude retrograde filling material placement. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:1000029
name: billing code for endodontic retreatment
is_a: CDT:1000030 ! billing code for endodontics
property_value: cdt:label "endodontic retreatment" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "This procedure may include the removal of a post, pin(s), old root canal filling material,\nand the procedures necessary to prepare the canals and place the canal filling. This\nincludes complete root canal therapy. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: CDT:1000030
name: billing code for endodontics
is_a: CDT:1000001 ! current dental terminology code
property_value: cdt:label "endodontics" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Local anesthesia is usually considered to be part of Endodontic procedures. \n\n ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

