[Term]
id: IDO:0000625
name: establishment of localization in host
def: "An establishment of localization process in which a material entity reaches a site in an organism in which it can survive, grow, multiply, or mature." []
comment: An organism begins bearing a particular host role as soon as the extended organism contains the relevant material entity, regardless of that entity's location in the extended organism.  An establishment process is any process by which the entity reaches a location in the extended organism in which it can persist and continue its lifecycle.  For example, an organism is host to a virus as soon as any part of the extended organism is occupied by virus particles.  During an establishment process, virus particles enter host cells of the relevant type, and viral DNA is integrated into host DNA.
is_a: GO:0051234 ! establishment of localization
property_value: editor_note "Requested addition of this term to the GO." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "Albert Goldfain" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "Alexander Diehl" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "Lindsay Cowell" xsd:string
property_value: isDefinedBy http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ido.owl

[Term]
id: IDO:0000626
name: appearance of disorder
def: "A process by which a disorder comes into existence." []
is_a: BFO:0000015 ! process
property_value: IAO:0000117 "Albert Goldfain" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "Alexander Diehl" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "Lindsay Cowell" xsd:string
property_value: isDefinedBy http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ido.owl

[Term]
id: MF:0000019
name: perception
def: "A mental process which is \na) produced by a causal process involving a part of the environment of the organism, and \nb) is experienced by the organism as being so caused, and \nc) in which the relevant part of the environment is thereby represented to the organism." []
comment: Examples for 'causal processes involving a part of the environment of an organism' that can be perceived are light rays and air vibrations.
is_a: MF:0000020 ! mental process
property_value: isDefinedBy mf:import.owl

[Term]
id: MF:0000020
name: mental process
def: "A bodily process that occurs in the brain, and that can of itself be conscious, or can give rise to a process that can of itself be conscious or can give rise to behaviour." []
comment: A 'mental process' is a subclass of 'bodily process', as mental processes occur within the body, specifically involving the brain.
comment: A bodily process which brings into being, sustains or modifies a cognitive representation or a behavior inducing state.
comment: Examples include thinking, feeling pain, remembering and emotion as occurrent experiences.
comment: Mental processes can varying in the degree to which they involve consciousness.
is_a: OGMS:0000060 ! bodily process
property_value: isDefinedBy mf:import.owl
property_value: seeAlso "GO:0050890, cognition, defined as  `The operation of the mind by which an organism becomes aware of objects of thought or perception; it includes the mental activities associated with thinking, learning, and memory.' " xsd:string

[Term]
id: MF:0000024
name: seeing
def: "Seeing (visual perception) is a mental process that is\na) produced by a causal process involving light rays from a part of the environment of the subject being absorbed by photoreceptors in the retina, and\nb) is experienced by the subject as being so caused, and\nc) in which the relevant part of the environment is thereby represented to the subject" []
is_a: MF:0000019 ! perception
property_value: IAO:0000118 "act of seeing" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000118 "visual perception" xsd:string
property_value: isDefinedBy mf:import.owl

[Term]
id: MF:0000038
name: hearing
def: "Hearing (auditory perception) is a mental process that is\na) produced by a causal process involving sound waves from a part of the environment of the subject being absorbed by detectors in the ear, and\nb) is experienced by the subject as being so caused, and\nc) in which the relevant part of the environment is thereby represented to the subject" []
is_a: MF:0000019 ! perception
property_value: IAO:0000118 "act of hearing" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000118 "auditory perception" xsd:string
property_value: isDefinedBy mf:import.owl

[Term]
id: MF:0000054
name: tasting
def: "Taste perception is a mental process which is\na) produced by a causal process involving xenobiotic molecules from a part of the environment of the subject binding with specialized sensory cells in the tongue and nasal cavity, and\nb) is experienced by the subject as being so caused, and\nc) in which the relevant part of the environment is thereby represented to the subject" []
is_a: MF:0000019 ! perception
property_value: IAO:0000118 "act of tasting" xsd:string
property_value: isDefinedBy mf:import.owl

[Term]
id: MF:0000055
name: smelling
def: "Smelling (olfactory perception) is a mental process which is\na) produced by a causal process involving xenobiotic molecules from a part of the environment of the subject binding with specialized sensory cells in the nasal cavity, and\nb) is experienced by the subject as being so caused, and\nc) in which the relevant part of the environment is thereby represented to the subject" []
is_a: MF:0000019 ! perception
property_value: IAO:0000118 "act of smelling" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000118 "olfactory perception" xsd:string
property_value: isDefinedBy mf:import.owl

[Term]
id: MF:0000056
name: touching
def: "Touching (tactile perception) is a mental process which is\na) produced by a causal process involving pressure on the organism’s skin from a part of the environment of the subject, and\nb) is experienced by the subject as being so caused, and\nc) in which the relevant part of the environment is thereby represented to the subject" []
is_a: MF:0000019 ! perception
property_value: IAO:0000118 "act of touching" xsd:string
property_value: isDefinedBy mf:import.owl

