property_value: isDefinedBy http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ogms.owl

[Term]
id: OGMS:0000100
name: inpatient encounter
def: "A health care encounter involving a patient who has been admitted to a health care facility and remains in a hospital facility for at least one night." []
is_a: OGMS:0000097 ! health care encounter
property_value: curator_notes "creation date: 2011-02-21T09:57:44Z" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "Albert Goldfain" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000119 "http://groups.google.com/group/ogms-discuss/browse_thread/thread/a2dbc2ed1dff99d6" xsd:string
property_value: isDefinedBy http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ogms.owl

[Term]
id: OGMS:0000101
name: emergency department encounter
def: "A health care encounter in which care is provided for undifferentiated and unscheduled patients with illnesses or injuries requiring immediate medical attention." []
is_a: OGMS:0000097 ! health care encounter
property_value: curator_notes "creation date: 2011-02-21T09:57:44Z" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "Albert Goldfain" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000119 "http://groups.google.com/group/ogms-discuss/browse_thread/thread/a2dbc2ed1dff99d6" xsd:string
property_value: isDefinedBy http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ogms.owl

[Term]
id: OGMS:0000102
name: injury
def: "A disorder that involves some structural damage that is immediately caused by a catastrophic external force." []
is_a: OGMS:0000045 ! disorder
property_value: curator_notes "creation date: 2011-09-20T09:57:44Z\nedited date: 30 SEPT 2015" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "At the scale of organism (as opposed to the cellular scale or the population scale), an injury is typically the result of a catastrophic event. Consider the implications of making 'injury' a subtype of 'disorder'.\n\nNote: Adopted subtype of disorder, and injury can occur at the scale of organism down to cellular level." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "Albert Goldfain\nSagar Jain" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000119 "http://groups.google.com/group/ogms-discuss/browse_thread/thread/ca0ad373f27774c5\n\nOGMS call adoption- 16 SEPT 2015\nhttps://docs.google.com/document/d/1iiV1-fTS7BUUSzDw3N_Afx42698YWf54-FOTY2NkAxo/edit" xsd:string
property_value: isDefinedBy http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ogms.owl

[Term]
id: OGMS:0000103
name: disease prophylaxis
def: "A planned process whose completion is hypothesized by a health care provider to reduce the risk of developing a disorder or the signs and symptoms of a disorder." []
is_a: OBI:0000011 ! planned process
property_value: curator_notes "creation date: 2011-09-20T09:57:44Z" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Whether or not 'prophylaxis' and 'treatment' classes are disjoint is an open question." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "Albert Goldfain" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000119 "http://groups.google.com/group/ogms-discuss/browse_thread/thread/e42bde79218ee34e" xsd:string
property_value: isDefinedBy http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ogms.owl

[Term]
id: OGMS:0000104
name: diagnostic process
def: "A health care process that involves the interpretation of a clinical picture from a given patient (input) and the assertion to the effect that the patient has a disease, disorder, or syndrome of a certain type, or none of these (output)." []
is_a: OGMS:0000096 ! health care process
relationship: part_of OGMS:0000096 ! health care process
property_value: curator_notes "creation date: 2011-09-20T09:57:44Z" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "Albert Goldfain" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000119 "http://groups.google.com/group/ogms-discuss/browse_thread/thread/2a7008f311fac766/e7de486c94dfd82e" xsd:string
property_value: isDefinedBy http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ogms.owl

[Term]
id: OGMS:0000108
name: health care process assay
def: "A health care process with the objective to produce information about the material entity that is the evaluant, by physically examining it or its proxies." []
is_a: OGMS:0000096 ! health care process
property_value: dc:date "creation: 16MAY2017" xsd:string
property_value: dc:publisher "Sagar Jain" xsd:string
property_value: isDefinedBy http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ogms.owl

[Term]
id: OGMS:0000123
name: clinical data item
def: "A data item that is about a patient and is the specified output of a health care process assay or diagnostic process" []
is_a: IAO:0000027 ! data item
property_value: curator_notes "creation date: 2018-11-27" xsd:string
property_value: isDefinedBy http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ogms.owl

[Term]
id: OGMS:0000129
name: physical sign
def: "An abnormal material entity that is part of a patient and hypothesized to be clinically relevant." []
is_a: BFO:0000040 ! material entity
property_value: curator_notes "Example: an abnormal growth, an inflammatory infiltrate, swollen tissue, distension" xsd:string
property_value: isDefinedBy http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ogms.owl

[Term]
id: OHD:0000000
name: dental restoration material
def: "A processed material that bears a dental restoration material role." []
is_a: OBI:0000047 ! processed material
relationship: BFO:0000053 OHD:0000191 ! is bearer of dental restoration material role
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: IAO:0000118 "restoration material" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000001
name: amalgam dental restoration material
def: "A metal dental restoration material that consists of alloy that is formed by reacting mercury with silver, copper, tin and sometimes palladium, zinc and other elements to improve handling characteristics and clinical performance." [] {IAO:0000119="ISBN: 978-1-4377-2418-9"}
comment: Color depends on which metal is in the alloy at what % (e.g. if copper is more, amalgam become blackish).
is_a: OHD:0000048 ! metal dental restoration material
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-6424-4096
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1829-971X
property_value: editor_note "Titus Schleyer 1/14/2014: updated definition" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000002
name: dental procedure
def: "A healthcare encounter that realizes a dental patient role in which the patient undergoes a diagnostic or therapeutic process." []
is_a: OGMS:0000097 ! health care encounter
is_a: OHD:0008039 {is_inferred="true"} ! process during dental visit
intersection_of: BFO:0000015 ! process
intersection_of: BFO:0000055 OHD:0000052 ! realizes dental healthcare provider role
intersection_of: BFO:0000055 OHD:0000190 ! realizes dental patient role
relationship: BFO:0000055 OHD:0000052 ! realizes dental healthcare provider role
relationship: BFO:0000055 OHD:0000190 ! realizes dental patient role
relationship: RO:0002092 OHD:0000009 ! happens during dental visit
property_value: editor_note "Bill Duncan 5/12/2015:\n\nChanged \"A specific healthcare activity\" to \"A health care encounter in which\"" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Titus Schleyer 1/14/14: adapted definition slightly" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "PERSON:Pedro Cott" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000003
name: endodontic procedure
def: "A dental procedure that is performed on the pulp chamber and/or root canal of a tooth, or a part thereof." []
is_a: OHD:0000002 {is_inferred="true"} ! dental procedure
relationship: RO:0000057 NCBITaxon:9606 ! has participant Homo sapiens
relationship: RO:0000057 UBERON:0001091 ! has participant calcareous tooth
property_value: editor_note "Titus Schleyer 1/14/2014: adapted definition" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "PERSON:Pedro Cott" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000004
name: tooth restoration procedure
def: "A dental procedure in which either a whole tooth or a part of a tooth is replaced by dental restoration material in order to reestablish the tooth's anatomical and functional form and function." []
is_a: OHD:0000002 ! dental procedure
relationship: BFO:0000055 OHD:0000007 ! realizes tooth to be restored role
relationship: OBI:0000417 OBI:0000434 ! achieves_planned_objective adding material objective
relationship: RO:0000057 UBERON:0001091 ! has participant calcareous tooth
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: editor_note "Bill Duncan 12/16/2014:\nUpdated definition. \n\nOriginal defintion:\nA dental procedure in which a part of a tooth that has been lost due to disease, trauma or other causes is replaced by dental restoration material in order to reestablish the tooth's anatomical form and function.\nA tooth restoration procedure achieves some tooth restoration objective specification.\n\n1. Added \"either a whole tooth or part of a tooth\", since implants and pontics are also restoration procedures.\n\n2. Removed \"that has been lost due to disease, trauma or other causes\". This is information about why a restoration procedure may be performed, not necessarily what such a procedure is." xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Bill Duncan:\nRemoved axiom for tooth restoration procedure that has specified output some \"has_part some  (Tooth and ('has role' some 'tooth to be restored role'))\". \n\nMy reasons for doing this are:\n1) the 'has role' axiom looks wrong. The restoration process realizes the role, but it sounds odd for the process to output the role.\n\n2) Since the tooth restoration process outputs a restored tooth, a restored tooth by definition/axiom has part some (tooth and dental restoration material)." xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Mosby's Dental Dictionary 2nd ed" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Titus Schleyer 3/14/2014: slightly edited definition" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "PERSON:Alan Ruttenberg" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "PERSON:Pedro Cott" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000005
name: surgical procedure
def: "A series of steps followed in a regular, orderly, definite way, performed by a physician, dentist or surgeon by manual operation." []
is_a: OGMS:0000097 ! health care encounter
property_value: editor_note "Titus Schleyer 3/4/2014: adapted definition" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "PERSON:Pedro Cott" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000119 "Mosby's Dental Dictionary 2nd ed" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000006
name: intracoronal restoration procedure
def: "A tooth restoration procedure in which a dental restoration material is placed into a site that is located in the crown of the tooth.\n" []
is_a: OHD:0000004 ! tooth restoration procedure
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: editor_note "Titus Schleyer 1/14/2014: updated definition" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "PERSON: Alan Ruttenberg" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000118 "filling restoration" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000007
name: tooth to be restored role
def: "A target of material addition role that inheres in a tooth and is realized by a tooth restoration procedure during which the tooth bearing the role is restored to health." []
is_a: OBI:0000444 ! target of material addition role
relationship: BFO:0000052 OHD:0000206 ! inheres in functional tooth
relationship: BFO:0000054 OHD:0000004 ! realized in tooth restoration procedure
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899

[Term]
id: OHD:0000008
name: tooth to be filled role
def: "A tooth to be restored role that is realized by an intracoronal restoration procedure" []
is_a: OHD:0000007 {is_inferred="true"} ! tooth to be restored role
intersection_of: OHD:0000007 ! tooth to be restored role
intersection_of: BFO:0000054 OHD:0000006 ! realized in intracoronal restoration procedure
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899

[Term]
id: OHD:0000009
name: dental visit
def: "An outpatient encounter during which a dental health care professional and a patient meet for the purpose of evaluating, treating disorders of, or preventing deterioration of the patient's oral health." []
is_a: OGMS:0000099 ! outpatient encounter
relationship: BFO:0000055 OHD:0000052 ! realizes dental healthcare provider role
property_value: editor_note "Titus Schleyer 1/14/14: adapted definition" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "PERSON:Alan Ruttenberg" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000119 "Adapted from Mosby's Dental Dictionary" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000010
name: dental finding
def: "A clinical finding is a specified output of a dental exam and is about the oral cavity, maxillofacial area, and/or the adjacent and associated structures, or their parts, or pathological anatomical entities derived from them. The finding has a part that is about when the exam that led to the finding occured well as other data items specifying the nature of the finding.\n" []
comment: replace tooth in logical def with dentition or mouth when it's been imported.
relationship: has_part IAO:0000027 ! data item
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: editor_note "Alan Ruttenberg 4/12/2012:\nFirst version of adapted definition by Bill:\nA dental observation regarding (or about) the evaluation, diagnosis, and/or treatment (nonsurgical, surgical, or related procedures) of diseases, disorders, and/or conditions of the oral cavity, maxillofacial area, and/or the adjacent and associated structures and their impact on the body; provided by dental professionals, within the scope of his/her education, training , and experience, in accordance with the ethics of the profession and applicable law" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Alan Ruttenberg 4/12/2012: The part of the finding that is specification of the time when it was created, is currently represented using the data property\n'occurence date'." xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Titus Schleyer1/14/2014: made a minor modification to the definition. This particular definition brings up the issue of language. This one is written in a very \"ontology-compliant\" way (\"... specified output of ...\"). The question is to what degree this would be understandable to the layman." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "Person:Alan Ruttenberg" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000119 "Adapted from Mosby's definition of dentistry:\nThe evaluation, diagnosis, and/or treatment (nonsurgical, surgical, or related procedures) of diseases, disorders, and/or conditions of the oral cavity, maxillofacial area, and/or the adjacent and associated structures and their impact on the body; provided by dental professionals, within the scope of his/her education, training, and experience, in accordance with the ethics of the profession and applicable law.\n(Mosby. Mosby's Dental Dictionary, 2nd Edition. Mosby, 102007. p. 173)." xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000011
name: performing a dental clinical assessment
def: "A diagnostic process in which a physician engages in a medical evaluation of teeth, gums, and other structures closely related to mastication." []
