[Term]
id: OHD:0000021
name: carious tooth lesion
def: "A tooth disorder that affects a tooth that includes both the infectious organisms, the material they generate from the tooth, any immune effectors that are a response to the presence of the disorder and the physical changes to the tooth (i.e., demineralization or a cavity) resulting from the disorder. It is the physical basis for the disease \"dental caries.\"" []
comment: is caries a material entity or a quality?\n
is_a: OHD:0000260 ! tooth disorder
relationship: RO:0002353 OHD:0000442 ! output of bacterial tooth demineralization process
relationship: RO:0002354 OHD:0000442 ! formed as result of bacterial tooth demineralization process
property_value: editor_note "Titus Schleyer 1/14/2014: updated definition" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "Titus Schleyer" xsd:string

