[Term]
id: OHD:0000024
name: caries finding
def: "A dental finding that indicates a carious lesion of a tooth" []
is_a: OHD:0000010 ! dental finding
relationship: IAO:0000136 OHD:0000021 ! is about carious tooth lesion
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: editor_note "Titus Schleyer 1/14/2014: How about this as an alternative definition: \"A dental finding that indicates a carious lesion of a tooth\"?" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000025
name: hard tissue exam
def: "A dental exam which includes a complete examination of hard tissues, specifically the teeth. It is performed tooth by tooth and documents aspects such as whether the tooth is missing or not, and its condition. A tooth is typically considered healthy if it is in a virgin state, or has one or more restorations that restore it to full morphology and function. Pathological conditions may include carious lesions, fractures, defective restorations, excessive wear and malpositions." []
is_a: OHD:0000019 ! dental exam
property_value: editor_note "Titus Schleyer 1/14/14: essentially rewrote definition and removed outdated citation to source" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "Person:Alan Ruttenberg" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000026
name: missing tooth finding
def: "A dental finding that notes the absence of a tooth that is canonically found, as identified by the universal tooth number.  The criteria for determing that a tooth is missing includes its absence in a visual exam, a radiographic exam or both. Thus, an unerrupted tooth seen in a radiograph is not considered missing." []
comment: to think about the proper logical definition: probably there is lacks_part to be fixed
is_a: OHD:0000010 ! dental finding
relationship: has_part OHD:0000100 ! obsolete Universal tooth number
relationship: IAO:0000136 UBERON:0007774 {cardinality="1"} ! is about secondary dentition
property_value: editor_note "Bill Duncan 4/12/2012: To think about: There are two cases at least - one where the tooth was never formed in the mouth and the other where the tooth was lost through some process.  Presently we do not distinquish between these cases." xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Bill Duncan 5/14/2012: Our criteria for determing that a tooth is missing is stronger than the clinical criterion.  Clinically, a tooth is missing if it is not visible in the oral cavity, in which case an unerrupted tooth is considered missing.  However, we include the added criterion that the tooth must also not be present in a radiograph.  Thus, if such an exam reveals the presence of such a tooth, the tooth is not considered to be missing." xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Bill Duncan 5/14/2012: We have added the necessary condtion that a missing tooth finding is about 'exactly 1 Secondary Dentition'.  " xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Titus Schleyer 1/14/2014: This might be a minor point, but clinically the two cases of \"tooth missing on visual clinical inspection\" and \"tooth missing on visual clinical inspection AND on radiograph\" might often be conflated in clinical documentation.  For instance, if a practitioner does not obtain radiographs,  she cannot really find the \"ground truth.\"" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000027
name: veneer restoration procedure
def: "A tooth restoration procedure in which a thin layer of material (i.e., a veneer) is placed over one or more surfaces of the tooth either to improve the aesthetics of the tooth or to protect the tooth's surface from damage" []
is_a: OHD:0000004 ! tooth restoration procedure
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: IAO:0000119 "Adapted from Wikipedia:\nhttp://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Veneer_%28dentistry%29" xsd:string

