[Term]
id: OHD:0000031
name: dental caries
def: "An infectious disease realized in a disease course during which a carious lesion develops in a tooth, resulting in demineralization, loss of tooth structure/appearance of a cavity or other structural damage to the tooth." []
is_a: IDO:0000436 ! infectious disease
relationship: BFO:0000054 OHD:0000443 ! realized in dental caries disease course
relationship: RO:0004020 OHD:0000420 ! disease has basis in dysfunction of oral microbial dysbiosis
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1604-3078
property_value: editor_note " Titus Schleyer 3/4/2014: definition updated" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Alan Ruttenberg 4/12/2012: We need to hook up the disease with the material basis, and possible a representation of the disease course. However we don't have the 'has material basis' relation yet, and its not clear that it is useful to represent the disease course." xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Bill Duncan 6/26/2015:\nThe old uri was DOID_216. I assume this class is intended to be an import from the disease ontology.\nThe uri was changed for backward compatabilty in the r21 study." xsd:string

