relationship: part_of OHD:0000019 ! dental exam
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: editor_note "This class was created in order to associate oral evaluations with dental findings that came about as the result of a dental exam. The data source I am working with has records that show multiple oral evalutions were performed on the same day. For example, the data source may have records that show a periodic oral evaluation, comprehensive oral evaluation, and comprehensive periodontal evaluation are performed on the same day. However, the finding(s) for these evaluations is/are stored in a separate table with only the patient id and date to associate the finding with the exam. There is no information to link the finding to a particular evaluation. \n\nAs a work around (i.e., hack!), I've made oral evaluations be part of the dental examination. There is a case to be made that oral evaluations should be a subclass of dental exam, but, such a representation, would make representing the finding information (associated with a particular oral evaluation) difficult." xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Titus Schleyer 1/14/2014: updated definition\n\nAlso, regarding Bill's comment on the fact that multiple examinations can occur on the same day (e.g.  periodic oral evaluation, comprehensive oral evaluation and comprehensive periodontal evaluation): From a billing and clinical perspective,  these are separate. For instance, a comprehensive oral evaluation has a larger scope than a periodic oral evaluation, while a  comprehensive periodontal evaluation is focused primarily on gums and supporting tissues." xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000198
name: periodic oral evaluation
def: "An oral evaluation performed on a patient of record (at an interval specified by the dentist) to determine any changes in the patients dental and medical health status since a previous evaluation. It includes an oral cancer evaluation and periodontal screening where indicated, and may require interpretation of information acquired through additional diagnostic procedures." []
is_a: OHD:0000197 ! oral evaluation
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: editor_note "Titus Schleyer 1/1/2014: updated definition" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000119 "ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000199
name: prefabricated resin crown restoration procedure
def: "a resin crown restoration procedure in which the artificial crown has been produced beforehand" []
is_a: OHD:0000154 ! resin crown restoration procedure
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: IAO:0000117 "a resin crown restoration procedure in which the artificial crown has been produced beforehand" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000200
name: no oral health issues reported
def: "A dental finding in which there were no oral health issues were reported." []
is_a: OHD:0000010 ! dental finding
property_value: editor_note "The intent of the class is to represent those case in which a dental exam is performed on patient, no finding is reported for the exam.  This could mean that the patients mouth is healthy; the patient had an issue but the examiner failed to report it; or (perhaps) that the patient has some oral health issue, but there are no new issues to report.\n\nThe label of the class may need to be changed." xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Titus Schleyer 1/14/2014: added \"issue\" to definition" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "a role that inheres in a person who licensed to provide health care" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "Bill Duncan" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000117 "PERSON: Bill Duncan" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000201
name: limited oral evaluation
def: "An oral evaluation limited to a specific oral health problem or complaint. This may require interpretation of information acquired through additional diagnostic procedures. Typically, patients receiving this type of evaluation present with a specific problem and/or dental emergencies, trauma, acute infections, etc." []
is_a: OHD:0000197 ! oral evaluation
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: IAO:0000119 "ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000202
name: comprehensive oral evaluation
def: "An oral evaluation that is performed on new patients; established patients who have had a significant change in health conditions or other unusual circumstances; or established patients who have been absent from active treatment for three or more years. It is a thorough evaluation and recording of the extraoral and intraoral hard and soft tissues. It may require interpretation of information acquired through additional diagnostic procedures. \n\nThis includes an evaluation for oral cancer where indicated, the evaluation and recording of the patients dental and medical history and a general health assessment.  It may include the evaluation and recording of dental caries, missing or unerupted teeth, restorations, existing prostheses, occlusal relationships, periodontal conditions (including periodontal screening and/or charting), hard and soft tissue anomalies, etc. " []
is_a: OHD:0000197 ! oral evaluation
relationship: has_part OHD:0000025 ! hard tissue exam
relationship: has_part OHD:0000204 ! intraoral soft tissue exam
relationship: has_part OHD:0000205 ! extraoral soft tissue exam
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: editor_note "Titus Schleyer 1/1/2014: checked definition, looks okay" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000119 "ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000203
name: comprehensive periodontal evaluation
def: "An oral evaluation performed on patients showing signs or symptoms of periodontal disease and for patients with risk factors for such disease, such as smoking or diabetes.  It includes evaluation of periodontal conditions, probing and charting, evaluation and recording of the patients dental and medical history and general health assessment.  It may include the evaluation and recording of dental caries, missing or unerupted teeth, restorations and occlusal relationships. " []
is_a: OHD:0000197 ! oral evaluation
relationship: has_part OHD:0000204 ! intraoral soft tissue exam
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: editor_note "Titus Schleyer 1/1/2014: slightly updated definition" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000119 "ISBN:1935201387#CDT 2011-2012 Current Dental Terminology, Chapter 1" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000204
name: intraoral soft tissue exam
def: "a physical examination of the soft tissue of the mouth, including the lips, mucosa, hard and soft palate, tongue, and floor of mouth" []
is_a: OHD:0000032 ! soft tissue exam
property_value: editor_note "technically I don't need to include giniva since it is mucosa, but felt like it in the interest of avoiding questions" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000119 "Alan Ruttenberg" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000119 "http://www.dentistry.utoronto.ca/dpes/diagnostic/patients/extraoral-and-intraoral-soft-tissue-examination-patient" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000205
name: extraoral soft tissue exam
def: "a physical examination of the soft tissue of the head and neck with attention to the temporomandibular joint area" []
is_a: OHD:0000032 ! soft tissue exam
property_value: IAO:0000117 "Alan Ruttenberg" xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000119 "http://www.dentistry.utoronto.ca/dpes/diagnostic/patients/extraoral-and-intraoral-soft-tissue-examination-patient" xsd:string

