[Term]
id: OHD:0000229
name: hemisection procedure
def: "A surgical endodontic procedure involving a multi-root tooth in which the decayed root and its related coronal portion are removed to the furcation (area of bone loss)." []
is_a: OHD:0000243 ! surgical endodontic procedure
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: editor_note "Bill Duncan 12/29/2016:\nTypically the removal of root/crown/bone is followed by the placement of an indirect restoration." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000119 "http://medical-dictionary.thefreedictionary.com/hemisection" xsd:string
creation_date: 2022-12-06T02:30:43Z

[Term]
id: OHD:0000230
name: endodontic treatment procedure
def: "A restored tooth in which the tooth's pulp is removed and replaced by dental restoration material." []
is_a: OHD:0000242 ! endodontic restorative procedure
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: IAO:0000118 "root canal treatment procedure" xsd:string
creation_date: 2022-12-06T02:21:35Z

[Term]
id: OHD:0000231
name: surgically modified tooth
def: "A tooth that has been modified in some way as the result of some surgical dental procedure." []
is_a: UBERON:0001091 {is_inferred="true"} ! calcareous tooth
intersection_of: UBERON:0001091 ! calcareous tooth
intersection_of: OBI:0000312 OHD:0000044 ! is_specified_output_of surgical dental procedure
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: editor_note "Bill Duncan 12/29/2016:\nThe intent of this class is to represent teeth that have undergone some kind of surgical procedure, but which are not restored in the sense of having dental restoration material placed in them; e.g, a pulp debridement procedure." xsd:string
property_value: example_of_usage "A tooth in which inflamed pulp has been removed by a pulp debridement procedure." xsd:string
creation_date: 2022-12-06T02:12:10Z

[Term]
id: OHD:0000232
name: pulpal debridement procedure
def: "A surgical endodontic procedure in which infected pulp is removed from a tooth in order to give the remaining pulp room to swell." []
is_a: OHD:0000243 ! surgical endodontic procedure
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: editor_note "Bill Duncan 12/29/2016:\nThis procedure relieves some of the pain, allowing a root canal patient to wait longer before having the full procedure performed." xsd:string
property_value: IAO:0000119 "http://www.ehow.com/facts_7478434_pulpal-debridement.html" xsd:string
creation_date: 2022-12-06T02:32:55Z

[Term]
id: OHD:0000233
name: extracted tooth
def: "A tooth that has been surgically extracted from a patient's mouth." []
is_a: UBERON:0001091 {is_inferred="true"} ! calcareous tooth
intersection_of: UBERON:0001091 ! calcareous tooth
intersection_of: OBI:0000295 OHD:0000057 ! is specified input of tooth extraction procedure
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: editor_note "Bill Duncan 12/29/2016:\nThis class represents those teeth which are extracted from a patient. After all, an extracted tooth is still a tooth. It just isn't part of the patient anymore.\n\nThis class provides us with a convient way to represent those teeth that have been extracted." xsd:string
creation_date: 2022-12-06T02:15:20Z

[Term]
id: OHD:0000235
name: restored facial surface
def: "A restored tooth surface that forms the lip-facing or cheek-facing surface of a restored tooth." []
is_a: OHD:0000208 {is_inferred="true"} ! restored tooth surface
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0009-0006-7251-3026
property_value: editor_note "Bill Duncan 01/05/2017:\nSome dental EHR systems use the letter \"F\" for facial surfaces rather than \"L\" for labial surfaces. The reason is that \"L\" is also used for the lingual surface." xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Gopikrishnan M. Chandrasekharan 07/12/2023:\nWe decided that the facial surface should subsume both labial and buccal surfaces." xsd:string
creation_date: 2022-12-06T02:42:40Z

