[Term]
id: OHD:0000261
name: tooth abfraction lesion
def: "A mechanical tooth lesion formed as a result of the tooth being fatigued, flexed, and deformed by biomechanical loading of the tooth. Tooth abfactions are primarily found in the cervical region of the tooth." [] {IAO:0000119="SNOMED CT \"Abfraction (disorder)\" (SCTID: 109750005)"}
is_a: OHD:0000271 ! mechanical tooth lesion
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0009-0006-7251-3026
property_value: dcterms:created "2023-06-06T21:30:59Z" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "Tooth abfractions are usually wedge-shaped lesions with sharp-line angles, but sometimes circular invaginations on occlusal surfaces." xsd:string
property_value: skos:exactMatch "SCTID:109750005" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0000262
name: tooth attrition lesion
def: "A tooth friction lesion that is caused by either the functional (e.g., mastication) or parafunctional movement of the jaws (e.g., bruxism)." []
is_a: OHD:0000290 ! tooth friction lesion
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0009-0006-7251-3026
property_value: dcterms:created "2023-06-06T21:31:20Z" xsd:dateTime
property_value: editor_note "The lesion are primarily found on the occlusal and incisal surfaces of the teeth, however it can be found on the proximal surfaces as well." xsd:string

