[Term]
id: OHD:0000290
name: tooth friction lesion
def: "A mechnical tooth lesion that formed as a result of some friction process." []
is_a: OHD:0000271 ! mechanical tooth lesion
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9625-1899
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0009-0006-7251-3026
property_value: dcterms:created "2023-06-22T21:30:59Z" xsd:string
property_value: editor_note "A tooth friction lesion is caused by a friction process involving an external object. For example, the clasp of an ill-fitting denture, pipe stem of a tobacco pipe, friction lesion of the interproximal areas caused by vigorous use of a tooth pick etc. An abrasive material is not involved in creating the friction lesion." xsd:string

