[Term]
id: OHD:0000442
name: bacterial tooth demineralization process
def: "A pathological bodily process during which tooth mineral is solubilized by acid produced by certain bacteria that adhere to the tooth surface in bacterial communities known as dental plaque." [] {IAO:0000119="https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK8259"}
is_a: OGMS:0000061 ! pathological bodily process
relationship: part_of OHD:0000443 ! dental caries disease course
