[Term]
id: OHD:0010133
name: glossopharyngeal neuralgia
def: "A disorder characterized by unilateral brief stabbing pain, abrupt in onset and termination, in the distributions not only of the glossopharyngeal nerve but also of the auricular and pharyngeal branches of the vagus nerve. Pain is experienced in the ear, base of the tongue, tonsillar fossa and/or beneath the angle of the jaw. It is commonly provoked by swallowing, talking or coughing and may remit and relapse in the fashion of Trigeminal neuralgia." []
comment: ICOP number: 4.2.1
subset: OHD:0010296
is_a: OHD:0010132 ! pain due to lesion or disease of the glossopharyngeal nerve
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0009-0003-5583-4731
property_value: dcterms:created "2025-06-18T17:56:55Z" xsd:dateTime
property_value: IAO:0000119 "PMID:32103673" xsd:string

