[Term]
id: OHD:0010299
name: trigeminal neuropathic pain
def: "Orofacial pain in the distribution of one or more branches of the trigeminal nerve. The primary pain is usually continuous or near-continuous, and commonly described as burning, squeezing, aching or likened to pins and needles." []
comment: ICOP number: 4.1.2
comment: related ICOP number: 4.1.2.4
comment: Superimposed brief pain paroxysms may occur but these are not the predominant pain type. This combination is distinct from that of 4.1.1 Trigeminal neuralgia. There are clinically detectable somatosensory changes within the trigeminal distribution, and mechanical allodynia and cold hyperalgesia/allodynia are common, fulfilling the IASP criteria for neuropathic pain. Allodynic areas may be much larger than the punctate trigger zones present in 4.1.1 Trigeminal neuralgia.
subset: OHD:0010296
synonym: "trigeminal neuropathic pain attributed to other disorder" RELATED []
is_a: OHD:0010059 ! pain due to lesion or disease of the trigeminal nerve
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0009-0002-7282-0836
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0009-0003-5583-4731
property_value: dcterms:created "2025-07-08T17:40:50Z" xsd:dateTime
property_value: IAO:0000119 "PMID:32103673" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0010300
name: trigeminal neuropathic pain attributed to herpes zoster
def: "Unilateral facial pain of less than 3 months’ duration in the distribution of one or more branches of the trigeminal nerve, caused by, and associated with other symptoms and/or clinical signs of, acute herpes zoster." []
comment: ICOP number: 4.1.2.1
subset: OHD:0010296
is_a: OHD:0010299 ! trigeminal neuropathic pain
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0009-0003-5583-4731
property_value: dcterms:created "2025-07-08T17:41:58Z" xsd:dateTime
property_value: IAO:0000119 "PMID:32103673" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0010301
name: trigeminal postherpetic neuralgia
def: "Unilateral facial pain persisting or recurring for at least 3 months in the distribution(s) of one or more branches of the trigeminal nerve, with variable sensory changes, caused by herpes zoster." []
comment: ICOP number: 4.1.2.2
subset: OHD:0010296
is_a: OHD:0010299 ! trigeminal neuropathic pain
property_value: dcterms:contributor https://orcid.org/0009-0003-5583-4731
property_value: dcterms:created "2025-07-08T17:42:37Z" xsd:dateTime
property_value: IAO:0000119 "PMID:32103673" xsd:string

[Term]
id: OHD:0010302
name: post-traumatic trigeminal neuropathic pain
def: "Unilateral or bilateral facial or oral pain following and caused by trauma to the trigeminal nerve(s), with other symptoms and/or clinical signs of trigeminal nerve dysfunction, and persisting or recurring for more than 3 months." []
comment: ICOP number: 4.1.2.3
subset: OHD:0010296
is_a: OHD:0010299 ! trigeminal neuropathic pain
